8. HOW KNOWLEDGE GETS INTO THE SYSTEM
==================================================

One of the strongest parts of the codebase is the knowledge ingestion pipeline.

In plain English, when an operator uploads a document, the system does not just save the file and stop.

It usually does all of the following:

1. store the raw file,
2. extract the readable text from it,
3. optionally improve that text for better AI retrieval,
4. split it into smaller searchable passages,
5. turn those passages into searchable numeric representations,
6. store the passages in the main database,
7. and store the search vectors in the vector database.

This is how Hivemind builds a searchable knowledge library.


8.1 Supported document types

The code supports more than just plain text files.

Based on the actual extraction and upload code, the current system handles:

- plain text,
- PDF,
- Word documents,
- and HTML.

This matters because the product is clearly built around feeding the AI curated source material.


8.2 Theory documents

Theory documents are the strategic or analytical reference materials.

Examples would be:

- strategic frameworks,
- business methodologies,
- analytical principles,
- or decision-making models.

These feed the theory side of Hivemind.


8.3 Practicality documents

Practicality documents are the realism-checking reference materials.

Examples would be:

- risk criteria,
- compliance rules,
- feasibility guidelines,
- regulatory constraints,
- or operational benchmarks.

These feed the practicality side of Hivemind.


8.4 Smart upload

There is also a "smart upload" workflow where the system tries to classify a document as theory-oriented or practicality-oriented before processing it.

In plain English:

- the operator gives it a document,
- the AI guesses whether the document is more about strategy or more about constraints,
- then the document is processed accordingly.


8.5 Pasted text workflow

The operator does not always need a file.

The code also allows text to be pasted directly into the knowledge system, then stored and indexed like an uploaded document.


8.6 Retrieval testing

The Admin app lets the operator test whether the system can find the right knowledge passages for a sample question.

This is an important quality check because the whole product depends on the AI finding the right background material at the right time.


