9. HOW SIMULATIONS FIT INTO THE PRODUCT
==================================================

The repository contains two simulation ideas at once.


9.1 Standalone formula-style simulations

These are clean, structured calculations with:

- inputs,
- formulas,
- outputs,
- tags,
- and a test runner.

Example:

- revenue and cost go in,
- profit and margin come out.

This simulation type is clearly supported in the Admin app and in the backend API.


9.2 Uploaded Python simulation programs with companion descriptions

There is also a second simulation workflow where the operator uploads:

- a Python program file,
- plus a companion explanation document.

The current code stores both, and it indexes the explanation document so it can be found during retrieval.

That means the repository is trying to support richer, code-based simulations in addition to simple formulas.

Important nuance:

- the standalone formula simulation workflow looks more complete and better surfaced in the current UI;
- the uploaded Python-program simulation flow is present, but its role in the live analysis path appears less fully matured.

In nontechnical terms: the product clearly wants AI units to use calculations when helpful, but the simpler calculation format looks more production-ready than the richer uploaded-program format.


