- "How many different final answer families am I willing to accept before the system stops debating?"

Feasibility threshold
- "How demanding should the reality-check be before an answer is rejected?"

Theory network density
- "How much source knowledge should each theory-side unit get?"

Dynamic density mode
- "Instead of me choosing the theory units manually, let the system try to build them automatically from the available knowledge."

Similarity threshold
- "How similar do two ideas need to be before the monitor lumps them together?"

Revision strength
- "How willing should each theory unit be to change its answer after receiving criticism?"

Practicality criticality
- "How harsh should the practicality judges be?"

Use-case profile
- A broad context such as small business, individual career, or enterprise.

Decision type
- A more specific decision category such as market entry, pricing, or M&A.

Manual agent selection
- The user can explicitly choose which theory and practicality units should participate.

These controls show that the product is not just returning a single canned AI response. It is exposing parts of the debate mechanism itself.


