13.2 Local all-in-one mode

At the same time, the Admin desktop shell still contains code to:

- initialize a local PostgreSQL data directory,
- start PostgreSQL locally,
- start Qdrant locally,
- start the Hivemind cloud server locally,
- and stop them again when the app exits.

This means the codebase still supports, or at least strongly remembers, a local bundled mode where a user can run much of the stack on their own machine.


13.3 Mac launchers and first-run setup

The repository includes:

- `Hivemind Admin.app`
- `Hivemind Client.app`
- `First Run Setup.command`

These are part convenience wrappers and part security workarounds for Mac.

The first-run setup script removes Mac quarantine/security restrictions and signs the launcher apps so they open more smoothly.

The launcher scripts also try to install missing dependencies and then start the apps from source.


13.4 Packaged exports

The `exports/` folder contains packaged `.pkg` installers and uninstallers for Admin, Client, and Cloud.

That tells us the team has also been experimenting with traditional installer distribution, not just developer-style launching from source.


